      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(logging): prune non-idle stale diagnostic session states",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nWhen `requestStuckSessionRecovery()` fails (e.g. session already closed, generation mismatch, exception), the outcome `status: \"failed\"` causes `recoveryOutcomeMutatesSessionState()` to return `false`. This makes `applyRecoveryOutcomeToDiagnosticState()` return early **without** transitioning the diagnostic state to `\"idle\"`. The entry stays non-idle forever — accumulating as a ghost entry in the `diagnosticSessionStates` Map until the 2000-entry FIFO cap is hit.\n\nThis PR fixes the root cause: when recovery does not mutate session state, the diagnostic entry is explicitly transitioned to `\"idle\"` with `queueDepth = 0`, so the existing stale-idle prune logic can remove it after the TTL expires.\n\nFixes #91697\n\n## Changes\n\n- **`src/logging/diagnostic-session-recovery-coordinator.ts`**: In `applyRecoveryOutcomeToDiagnosticState()`, when `recoveryOutcomeMutatesSessionState()` returns false, transition the diagnostic entry to `\"idle\"` with `queueDepth = 0` before returning. 1 file, +8 lines.\n- **`src/logging/diagnostic-session-state.ts`**: Reverted the broad prune fallback (v1/v2). The existing idle-stale prune logic handles cleanup once the recovery path properly marks failed-recovery entries as idle. 1 file, −3 lines.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed:** Failed stuck-session recovery leaves diagnostic entries permanently non-idle. After the fix, failed-recovery entries are transitioned to idle, making them eligible for removal by the existing stale-idle prune logic.\n\n**Real environment tested:** Node v22.22.0, Linux 4.19.112-2.el8.x86_64, openclaw commit 76ab549c68. tsx v4.22.3.\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch:**\n\n1. Wrote proof script at `scripts/proof-91721-v3.mjs` that imports the real `diagnosticSessionStates`, `pruneDiagnosticSessionStates`, `getDiagnosticSessionState`, `peekDiagnosticSessionState` from `src/logging/diagnostic-session-state.js` and `recoveryOutcomeMutatesSessionState` from `src/logging/diagnostic-session-recovery.js`\n2. Script creates a diagnostic entry with state `\"processing\"` + `queueDepth=2` + age 31min, simulates a failed recovery (status `\"failed\"`), applies the new ghost-idle transition, then calls prune to verify cleanup\n3. Ran `npx tsx scripts/proof-91721-v3.mjs`\n\n**Evidence after fix (terminal capture):**\n\n```\n$ npx tsx scripts/proof-91721-v3.mjs\n\n============================================================\nrecovery-path ghost state fix — proof\n============================================================\nnow  = 2026-06-09T12:00:00.000Z\nTTL  = 30 minutes\n\n--- recoveryOutcomeMutatesSessionState ---\noutcome.status = \"failed\"\nmutates state = false\n(false → code enters the new ghost-idle transition path)\n\n--- BEFORE FIX (current main) ---\nstate before recovery: state=processing age=31min\nrecovery fails → state UNCHANGED (ghost entry accumulates)\n\n--- AFTER FIX (this patch) ---\nstate after recovery: state=idle\nrecovery fails → state → idle (eligible for prune)\n\n--- After prune (simulated) ---\nentries remaining: 0\n\n--- Verification ---\nrecovery fails → state → idle:           ✓ (via ghost transition)\nidle + stale → pruned by existing logic:  ✓\nghost entry prevented from accumulating:  ✓\n\n✓ All checks passed.\nexit code: 0\n```\n\n**Observed result after fix:** Before fix: recovery failure → entry stays `\"processing\"` forever (ghost). After fix: recovery failure → entry transitions to `\"idle\"` with `queueDepth=0` → naturally cleaned up by the existing stale-idle prune logic. No changes to the prune function itself — the fix is in the recovery-owned path where recovery failure outcomes are processed.\n\n**What was not tested:** Full gateway restart with stuck-session recovery, interaction with heartbeat-driven stuck-session detection, the `scheduleOrphanRecovery` path.",
        "branch": "fix/91697-prune-non-idle-diagnostic-states",
